HEADWORD: Scutage
<hw>Scu"tage</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>scutagium</ets>, from L. <ets>scutum</ets> a shield.]</ety>
<fld>(Eng. Hist.)</fld> <def>Shield money; commutation of service for a
sum of money. See <er>Escuage</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

